rinciples of Shanker Self-Reg®: - There is no such thing as a bad, lazy, or stupid kid. - All people can learn to self-regulate in ways that promote rather than constrict growth. - There is no such thing as a "fixed outcome": trajectories can always be changed, at any point in the lifespan, if only we have the right knowledge and tools. Only a society that embraces these principles and strives to practice them, argues Shanker, can become a truly just society. The paradigm revolution presented in Reframed not only helps us understand the harrowing time we are living through, but inspires a profound sense of hope for the future. Shanker shows us how to build a compassionate society, one mind at a time.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aChild psychology. 0aSelf-controlxSocial aspects. 0aSelf-control. 0aSelf-management (Psychology). 0aStress (Psychology). 0aStress management. 4aDISCOUNT-C. 7aSELF-HELP / Self-Management / Stress Management.2bisacsh  afreedom.  agrit.  aintelligence.  amental health.  aparenting.  aresilience.  aschools.  aself-control.  aself-reg.  aself-regulation.  asocial justice.  awellbeing.  awillpower.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311069045340uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148753381640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487533816423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781487533816.jpg  a978-3-11-069045-3  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles